 Jacobi. Die Quellentexte werden durch einen textkritischen Apparat und einen reichhaltigen Stellenkommentar (Nachweis von Traditionsgut, Klärung prosopographischer, bibliographischer und historischer Sachverhalte) sowie durch editorische Berichte, Nachworte und Register präzise erschlossen. Ein umfänglicher Anhang bietet sämtliche verfügbaren (teils archivalischen) Dokumente zur Entstehungsgeschichte des Werkes und zur Kooperation Rists mit seinen Komponisten dar.  aThe Catechism Devotions are comprised of 50 spiritual songs that impart all of the material in Luther's Small Catechism in vocal form. They are regarded as an important milestone in early modern theologia catechetica that aimed at an elemental presentation of the liturgy.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aChurch musicxLutheran ChurchvEarly works to 1800. 0aHymns, Germany17th century. 4a17. Jahrhundert. 4aBarockliteratur. 4aDeutsche Literatur. 4aKirchenlieder. 7aRELIGION / Christian Ministry / Pastoral Resources.2bisacsh1 aHammerschmidt, Andreas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHernández Castelló, Esteban, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuck, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobi, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSteiger, Johann Anselm, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z97831107010050 cEPUBz